---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Netherlands Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/netherlands/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
  { title: 'Belgium for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/belgium' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'nlFit', header: 'Netherlands Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€410-585/mo', nlFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€480-685/mo', nlFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€365-520/mo', nlFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€340-485/mo', nlFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Dutch Basic (Zorgverzekering)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: '€130-160/mo', nlFit: 'Mandatory' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€365-585', annual: '€4,380-7,020' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€500-775', annual: '€6,000-9,300' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€675-1,040', annual: '€8,100-12,480' },
  { category: 'Dutch Basic Insurance', monthly: '€130-160/mo', annual: '€1,560-1,920' },
  { category: 'Supplemental Coverage', monthly: '€20-100/mo', annual: '€240-1,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Netherlands 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in the Netherlands. Excellent healthcare, English-speaking, cycling culture, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in the Netherlands"
  subheadline="The Netherlands offers excellent healthcare, widespread English, cycling culture, and high quality of life—one of Europe most English-friendly countries for retirement."
  heroImage="/images/countries/netherlands-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose the Netherlands</h2>
  <p>
    The Netherlands offers excellent healthcare, widespread English proficiency, cycling culture, and high quality of life. For English speakers seeking European retirement, the Netherlands is exceptionally accessible. The challenge is cost of living and flat, rainy climate.
  </p>

  <p>
    Amsterdam offers cosmopolitan living at premium cost. Rotterdam has modern architecture and port character. The Hague provides international community. Maastricht offers southern charm. Many towns offer quality living at lower cost. The country is compact and well-connected.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; mandatory insurance system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dutch; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,200-4,200/month (~$2,400-4,600); moderate-high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Maritime; mild but rainy</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Cycling; direct; tolerant</li>
      <li><strong>EU Member:</strong> Schengen; excellent transport links</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Netherlands Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    The Netherlands has mandatory health insurance—everyone must have basic coverage (zorgverzekering). Private insurers provide basic package at regulated price (~€130-160/month). Supplemental coverage available for extras. Quality is excellent with good access to specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    All residents must have Dutch basic insurance. Supplemental covers dental, physio, etc. €385 annual deductible for most care. System is efficient and high quality. International insurance may work for some situations but most residents need Dutch basic.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Insurance</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      The Netherlands requires basic health insurance for all residents. Premiums are ~€130-160/month regardless of age. €385 annual deductible applies. Care allowance (zorgtoeslag) available for lower incomes. System is mandatory but affordable.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Netherlands has various options:
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement—right to live in the Netherlands. Register at gemeente (municipality) after arrival.
  </p>

  <h3>Orientation Year Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those seeking opportunities. One-year visa to explore options. Some retirees use for transition.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    For family members of Dutch citizens or residents. Income requirements apply.
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employed/Entrepreneur</h3>
  <p>
    For those starting business or working independently. Points-based assessment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for the Netherlands:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residents:</strong> Dutch basic insurance mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> Must join Dutch system if resident</li>
    <li><strong>Supplements:</strong> Optional for dental, physio, glasses</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> May work for non-resident situations</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Netherlands</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      All residents must have Dutch basic insurance—mandatory, no exceptions. International insurance supplements but doesn't replace basic. Supplemental covers dental, physio. System is straightforward; choose basic insurer (all cover same package) plus supplements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in the Netherlands, Dutch basic insurance is mandatory:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Netherlands</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dutch basic:</strong> Mandatory for residents; CZ, Zilveren Kruis, VGZ</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Supplements basic for international coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> For non-resident periods or supplemental</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental:</strong> Dental, physio, international coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare supplemental coverage for the Netherlands.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Netherlands include mandatory basic:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Zorgtoeslag:</strong> Care allowance for lower incomes</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductible:</strong> Can increase above €385 for lower premium</li>
    <li><strong>Basic only:</strong> Dental/physio as out-of-pocket if rarely needed</li>
    <li><strong>Outside Randstad:</strong> Lower living costs in smaller cities</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Expat, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month pension. Self-employed visa. Amsterdam.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Dutch basic mandatory + CZ supplemental for dental.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Basic ~€145 + supplemental ~€35/month. English-friendly; canal living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Post-Brexit, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,600/month pension. Family reunification. Rotterdam.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Dutch basic + comprehensive supplemental. EU access.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Basic + supplemental ~€220/month. EU residence post-Brexit.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,400/month pension. EU free movement. The Hague.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Dutch basic (required). Allianz for international travel.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Basic ~€140 + Allianz ~€400/month. International city; familiar EU system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do Dutch people really speak English?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among world most proficient non-native English speakers. Healthcare, business, daily life all work in English. Dutch appreciate effort to learn but English is sufficient. One of Europe most accessible countries for English speakers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Dutch insurance really mandatory?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—all residents must have basic insurance within 4 months of arrival. Fines for non-compliance. Premiums are flat regardless of age (~€130-160). Zorgtoeslag helps lower incomes. System is mandatory but fair.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Dutch healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—consistently ranked among Europe best. Good access to GPs and specialists. Efficient system. University medical centers are excellent. English-speaking doctors available. Quality is genuine advantage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the Netherlands flat and rainy?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—very flat; much below sea level. Maritime climate means rain throughout year. Mild temperatures rarely extreme. Cycling culture embraced. Some find weather depressing; others appreciate mildness. Personal preference.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Netherlands coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Dutch authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
